A plug-in that can accurately identify the pros and cons of exchanges and project parties through exchanges, project parties, and token websites, and quickly understand the current market value of tokens.

In the face of numerous complex exchanges, project parties, and tokens, it is difficult for ordinary investors to use their own limited knowledge resources to identify and identify them, resulting in heavy losses when encountering unscrupulous exchanges, project parties, and tokens, and some even went bankrupt. WikiBit is committed to safeguarding the interests of global investors. It takes standardizing the trading market and promoting healthy development as its own responsibility. Relying on the massive professional big data resources that the company has mastered, combined with artificial intelligence computing, it has developed the SkyEye supervision plug-in.

This plug-in is adapted to the websites of various exchanges, project parties, and token platforms around the world.

This plugin includes simplified Chinese, traditional Chinese, English, French, Italian, Thai, Vietnamese and other languages.

Using this plug-in, when visiting an exchange, project party, or token website, the pop-up box in the lower right corner of the page will automatically display the exchange, project party, and token evaluation information. Automatically shrinks into a spherical logo after closing.

There is no registration required to use this plugin.

core function:
1. Display the supervision information of exchanges and project parties;
2. Display exchanges, project parties, and token ratings;
3. Display the exposure information of the exchange and projects;
4. Display the current market value of the token;
